X,Y
\left(x,y\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{2}
X,Y
\mathbb{P}\left(X\leq x,\, Y\leq y\right)\cdot\mathbb{P}\left(X\geq x,Y\geq y\right)=\mathbb{P}\left(X\geq x,Y\leq y\right)\cdot\mathbb{P}\left(X\leq x,Y\geq y\right)
P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)\left[1-P_{X}\left(x\right)-P_{Y}\left(y\right)+P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)\right]=\left[P_{Y}\left(y\right)-P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)\right]\left[P_{X}\left(x\right)-P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)\right]
P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)=P_{X}\left(x\right)P_{Y}\left(y\right)
P_{X}\left(x\right)=P\left\{ X\leq x\right\} 
P_{Y}\left(y\right)=P\left\{ Y\leq y\right\} 
P_{X,Y}\left(x,y\right)=P\left\{ X\leq x,Y\leq y\right\} 
\ge
>
